                "name": "Studio W King Bed By Walkable Sunset Strip* Month+",
                "description": "Studio apartment in trendy West Hollywood neighborhood. Only 1 block away from the Sunset Strip, Santa Monica Blvd, and farfaixs', restaurants, coffee shops bars and shops. \nYou can watch a movie from the king bed, work from home on the dedicated work desk, and walk down the block to cool restaurants, bars, malls and more.\nThe studio is furnished for 2 with all the equipment and essentials needed to enjoy a long stay.\nIncludes fast Wi-Fi, Netflix, & Cable TV.\n\nStudio with all the essentials to enjoy a long and comfortable stay.\nFast Wi-Fi and large smart TV with Netflix, cable and local TV.\nKitchen includes cookware and dining ware, microwave, toaster, coffee maker, electric kettle, and more.\nBathroom includes towels, toilet paper,  soaps, shampoo, and conditioner. \nExtra towels and bedding provided.\nCleaning  supplies also supplied.\nSurfaces are all sanitized.\nSimple studio and building with no shared spaces besides walkways.\n\nBeautiful suite and walkway balcony.\nStreet parking.\nNice laundromat 3 doors down with fluff and fold.\n\nFeel free to contact me before 9 PM and afterwards for emergencies, I respond to messages promptly.\n\n~There is self check in/out.\n\n-I usually dont come by the unit but do come by for emergencies.\n\nTruly a central, safe, fun, and quirky area with so much to see within walking distance or a quick drive. I'll give some quick highlights about the area but don't hesitate to inquire about something more specific.\n\nThis place is: \n-centrally located in a neighborhood full of coffee shops , restaurants,  bars , fashion stores \n-next door to convenience stores and a laundromat. \n- two blocks away from an outdoor mall with Trader's Joe's ' Starbucks , Crunch Gym and AMC theaters.\n-Melrose avenue, Santa Monica , Fairfax are all within walking distance .\n\nEven though this area is very walkable, it's best to have car or use Uber/Lyft (which is affordable in LA) to get around.\nThese days shared transportation methods are easily accessible like bikes to scooter.\nIf you bring a car there is street parking on the block - most of the time with a mid size sedan you can find parking within a few properties.\nDriving Destinations\nAirport - 30 to 45 minutes\nHollywood Walk of Fame - 5 to 10 minutes\nRunyon Canyon (beautiful hikes, views, and people) - 7 minutes\nCedar Sinai - 5 to 10 min\nUCLA and USC - 20 to 30 min\nSanta Monica Beach/Pier - 20 to 45 min (can take bus to train in 1 hour)\nUniversal Studios & City Walk - 10 to 20 min\n\nThis unit is on the 2nd floor in a typical Hollywood building from the '50s with its\ncharm and corkiness.\nThere is street parking  available --from in front of the building  to a few buildings down. I usually find it within a few buildings away depending on time of a day.\n\n This is a very well priced apartment for the area. I will only entertain an additional discount for stays over 6 months.",
