                "name": "Sweet West Hollywood Bungalow B/T Sunset & Melrose",
                "description": "Large, fully equipped private studio in a spectacular location: heart of West Hollywood--a couple of blocks from Fairfax @ Santa Monica Blvd. New queen bed & another queen sofa bed; full kitchen; bar; fast WiFi; new strong AC; big new 4K TV; K-cup coffee; \n\nEverything you need within short Walking distance (95 walk score). Whole Foods just up the street; close to Melrose boutiques, Sunset Strip, Fairfax District, Farmer's Market, Grove, Walk of Fame, bars/clubs, cafe's + many other hot spots!\n\nOne of the liveliest, most popular neighborhoods in all of LA.  All you need is within walking distance (95 walking score) or within a >$10 Uber ride.  Gorgeous, safe and close to everything fun and exciting. Gay friendly.\n\nThe unit is a couple of blocks from the Whole Foods on Santa Monica Blvd. at Fairfax Ave. Walking distance to both the Sunset Strip and the Weho clubs. Just up the street from the fabulous outdoor shopping complex The Grove, as well as the trendy Melrose shopping district. \n\nWithin easy walking distance are dozens of fantastic restaurants and cafes, a couple of grocery stores, liquor stores, dry cleaners, gyms, a dispensary and yoga studios. If you enjoy cooking, the unit comes with a full kitchen and basic cookware. Walk over to Whole Foods to get whatever you need. West Hollywood is also centrally located, so it’s an easy drive/Uber to Hollywood’s Walk of Fame, Venice Beach, Santa Monica, Universal Studios, LACMA, and the Getty.\n\nDelilah's, a 20s-themed restaurant/lounge with live music and burlesque dancers is just steps away. Also nearby is Connie & Ted's, a local's favorite seafood restaurant with a fun atmosphere and eclectic craft beer and wine offerings.  Hudson and Laurel Hardware are two beautiful people bars also within walking distance\n\nSanta Monica Blvd spots (2 blocks away):\nWhole Foods\nHarlowe\nLa Boheme\nEmployees Only ('20s style bar)\nBar Lubitsch\nHarlowe\nSchmitty's\nLaurel Hardware\nConnie and Ted's (seafood)\nHamburger Mary's\nEarth Bar\nStarbucks\nMoe's Cafe\nBarney's Beanery (classic old school diner/bar)\nOr Bar\n\nNearby Sunset Strip spots:\nPink Taco\nChateau Marmont & Chateau Hanare\nTower Bar\nThe Den\nPinches Tacos (fantastic late-night burritos!)\nSkyBar\nThe Standard Hotel\nMany more!\n\nIf you're coming without a car, you'll be fine. A car really isn't necessary in this location. It so close to shopping, restaurants and nightlife that using Uber/Lyft is very inexpensive. Cars typically arrive very quickly.\n\nIt's also walking distance to the #4 Bus line that runs East/West along Santa Monica Blvd. and multiple busses that run North/South along Fairfax Blvd.",
